  "rationale": "<p>Apply exponent rules: a^(3/4) / a^(−1/2) = a^(3/4 + 1/2) = a^(5/4). b^(−2) / b^(1/3) = b^(−2 − 1/3) = b^(−7/3). So the expression equals a^(5/4) · b^(−7/3) = a^(5/4) / b^(7/3) = ⁴√(a⁵) / (b² · ³√b). Choice (a) is correct.</p><p>Choice (b) uses a^(1/2), which corresponds to a^(5/2) not a^(5/4). Choice (c) shows a^(3/4) in the numerator, which corresponds to subtracting the exponents instead of adding them. Choice (d) drops the fractional parts entirely.</p>",
